<item>
            <title>[FLINK-31995] DirectExecutorService doesn&apos;t follow the ExecutorService contract throwing a RejectedExecutionException in case it&apos;s already shut down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31995</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We experienced an issue where we tested behavior using the &lt;tt&gt;DirectExecutorService&lt;/tt&gt; with the &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorService&lt;/tt&gt; being shutdown already. The tests succeeded. The production code failed, though, because we used a singleThreadExecutor for which the task execution failed after the executor was stopped. We should add this behavior to the &lt;tt&gt;DirectExecutorService&lt;/tt&gt; as well to make the unit tests be closer to the production code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
